 word is out on this place.  And it won't disappoint.  So why would I need to add one more review to an overwhelming outpouring of opinion?  Just to add some cautions:\n\n1) Make the chefs happy and go for the back of the menu where the specialties are.  Don't even think about ordering Pad Thai!\n\n2)  If you like Riesling, they have an overwhelming list.  But we always seem to get a bottle that has gone into secondary fermentation.  If you consider a bit of gas to be a fault (as I do), you'll likely have to return it for something else.  Or just give up and enjoy the bubbly!\n\n3)  Watch the temp on the spice, it gets hot FAST.  Bring facial tissues and enjoy the heat.\n\n4)  MAKE RESERVATIONS, ASAP!  While they seem to make every effort to accommodate those without, this place is ridiculously popular and will always be booked up.\n\n5)  Don't judge a book by its cover.  When you pull up, it will look like a dump.  The area is old, run down and looks a bit scary, though it's largely abandoned.  Go inside and you will find a nice restaurant.\n\nBut do go and try it.  It is really good if you order right!", "Don't see what's the big deal . Very simple place , super packed , 2 h waiting for just average quality food . Oh and you will be served so fast you lol be done in 10 min ... And you will be put under pressure to leave coz next person waiting .", "Every once in a while, we get the urge for salmon tartar....this is where we go! FANTASTIC!", "Every since I saw this restaurant from the food channel, I wanted to come here to try the authentic Thai food. I've been to Thailand only once so it is difficult to me to determine if the dish is authentic or not. But I can tell whether the dish is tasty or not. Thai tea was great. The dishes were very tasty. Unfortunately I don't remember the name of the dishes that I got but I will attach the photos of the food that I had. When I came here which was around 1:45pm, there was an hour wait so be aware of the lines that you need