 food came out pretty quickly. The food was pretty amazing. The beef dish had tons of spices (cilantro, mint, green onion, red onion - just to name a few) that worked well together. It was so good! Be careful how spicy you get it. We got it medium and our mouth was on fire at the end of the meal. The BBQ prawns were my favorite. The shrimp, which came with an amazing garlic pepper sauce, was so good and tender. Its definitely a must try. It's a little on the pricey side at $25 for 8 prawns, but I would definitely get it again. \n\nOverall, I am so glad that I decided to give this place a try. One minor complaint that I have is that we only saw our waiter twice, once to take out order and once to take our check. We ended up flagging down another waiter when we wanted to order additional rice. But, it was not too big of a deal as the other waiters was willing to help us.  I will definitely be back to try other dishes here. (There menu is very expansive and I would like to try other items).", "I came Las Vegas for vacation. This is real thai food (you need to order 10 hot stars).", "I came here again, because I know I can only have the best Thai food in Vegas outside of Thailand. It's a tourist trap, but it's 15 minutes from the strip & people still go here regardless of the difficulty to find the restaurant's awkward green light, shaded doors & dark plaza . \n\nWe followed Anthony Bordain's footsteps & tried their Thai curry noodles, ground pork as well as their sticky rice & pad Thai. Curry noodles were to die for!", "I came here with some friends while in Vegas. Chef Jet Tila made us a reservation, which he offered to do when I took his Thai town tour in LA, so I knew that it would be good! There were 5 of us and we ordered family style, starting with the summer spring roll special and papaya salad. I am a spicy girl, and those spring rolls were spicy! The papaya salad had perfect flavor, but it was a bit watery for my taste. For mains, we shared fried rice, panang 