ai and a massage at Wei Wei. Go to china town!!!", "Yum!  Love it!  We've been there many times. Don't be frightened by the location, once you are inside, it's all good.  The food is amazing and the wine selection is spectacular.  They even take special care in polishing the wine glasses... Classy!  It's always busy, better to make a reservation.", "\u0130stanbul da yasayan biri olarak thai food lar\u0131nda cokca deneyimliyim.. Dolay\u0131s\u0131yla cok enteresan gelmedi ama inan\u0131lmaz lezzetli.. vegas a gelirsen mutlaka ugranmas\u0131 gerekenler listene eklemelisin...", "damn this place is awesome, food is perfect and full of taste, i had to comeback and never regret", "delicious!  happy enviornment, quality dishes, knowledgable servers.  great experience!", "don't believe the hype. not all that.", "great Thai food.  need a reservation cause it's always packed.  komol a few doors down is a great alternative if you don't want to wait", "heard lots of hype about this place so i checked it out. the food is ok. but i expected more from a $300+ bill for 4 people.  lobster, shrimp, sticky rice, soups. average thai food. for the same money, there are better restaurant choices in the area.", "i love this place, i love everything about it...\nthe food is amazing\nthe servers are nice\nthe seating is comfy\nthe wine cooler is cool ;)\nbut, the prices!!!!! why do they keep going up? this is not cool.", "i need to go back, it's that good", "lots better Thai restaurants than this place. cant believe its a national rated place. took me a while to figure out why the deep fried veggies were light pink, Palm oil", "never expected this place to be so good, all the good reviews about this place are not lying !", "nom nomz. heard about this place through a friend who wanted to go try it. checked it out on Yelp and it is probably the highest rated Thai restaurant in all of Vegas. my group figured we HAD to go before we left Vegas. plus, i love Thai food anyways. \n\nBe prepared for an early dinner or plan when you're going and make reservations (you need to make them at least 7 days in advance). the restaurant opens at 5:30PM and the line is no joke. my friends and I had a large party so we got there at about 5PM and started waiting in line. I thought it was ridiculous that we went so early since we were the only ones waiting in line. lo and behold, 10 minutes later, the line was down the block. doors opened at 5:30PM and the reservations line gets seated first. then my party was first in line to get a table since we got there so early. i looked around as we ordered and the restaurant filled up quickly. \n\nthe restaurant is known for it's northern Thai food so leave the traditional Pad Thai at home. my party decided to order a bunch of food and just share it family style. we had 2 orders of their garlic prawns, the chicken khao soi (chicken served on a bed of egg noodles in a curry base sauce, garnished with sliced red onions, lime and pickled vegetables), nam kao tod (Crispy rice mixed with sour cubed pork sausages, cilantro, green onions, grounded dry chilis, ginger, peanuts and lime juice), drunken noodle soft shell crab, panang curry with crispy duck, and a beef dish... I believe it was the Pad Prik Sod (Choice of meat saut\u00e9ed with bell peppers, fresh chili pepper, & onions). we all also ordered the Thai Iced Tea which is delicious and highly recommended. I love that you can really taste the tea flavor yet it was still sweet and creamy. \n\nwhen the food came, we were all ready to chow down. they also gave us a basket of rice and said that if we needed more, we could just ask. the dishes seemed small but for some reason, we had a party of 8 and were still not able to finish all the food. everything was amazing and tasted super fresh. I would definitely recommend the garlic prawns and any dish with the crispy duck. \n\nof course we all wanted to get a dessert before we left so we ordered one mango sticky rice to share amongst us. th