uper spicy.  You get to choose the spiciness level from 1-10.  It was so good though.  The curry broth had so much explosive flavor.  The noodles were cooked perfectly, and all the ingredients inside the bowl complimented each other perfectly.  My favorite part of the dish was the coconut curry, hands down.  \n\nFor dessert, there are three options.  They are ice cream, fried bananas, and mango sticky rice.  We decided to get the ice cream AND fried bananas, which are two desserts.  I have to admit, I have not ever seen fried bananas served without ice cream.  It was surprising that people order it by itself.  When it finally arrived, we were already so full.  I wish there was more ice cream to go with the bananas.  We finished the ice cream with about four more banana pieces left.  \n\nOverall, a very good dining experience.  It was quite nice to get away from The Strip.  Out of the less than ten times I have been to Vegas, this was my first time eating outside  casinos and away from the gambling addicts.  It was a pleasant experience, and I can see why this place is doing so well.", "I was in Vegas for a business trip and my co-worker had been here before and I love Thai, so we made a reservation and went. It was absolutely delicious (and FREE on the company!). We got Prawns in a Blanket-- absolute must-try!, Beef in Tamarind sauce (also great), green curry, and a rice dish (I forgot which one, unfortunately). Service was great, atmosphere was chatty, but not too loud where we were seated, and I was surprised at how affordable it all was, although it's worth splurging a little in order to try lots of different things. If I visit LV again, I will definitely come here again! Definitely need reservations, though.", "I went here after a long day.  Now, the outside of the place, parking lot and surrounding areas are less than desirable.  However, the inside was a stark contrast.  It was very nice, bright and very clean.  I would definitely make a reservation.  The food