om the strip in a little mall- this is a hidden gem!\n\nThe food is all amazing! Delicious! And spice levels to your taste.\n\nThey specialize in Northern Thai- but anything on the menu if good.", "Was craving for Thai food and we went due to the Yelp reviews!  I usually order just my normal Thai dishes Beef Panang, Papaya Salad, Tom Kha, and Pad Thai. As I was eating I noticed the tables all around me ordered the Fried Garlic Shrimp and thought to myself do I wanna really spend $25.00 for a dish with 6-8 shrimps?????  Whoa was I wrong thee best $25.00 I spent on a shrimp fish and hands down the best Fried Shrimp I have had!!!  I will be back and just order two orders of the Shrimp and Pad Thai and I will be one happy camper!!!!", "Was driving through Las Vegas and have been wanting to go here for years and had to make the small detour. It did not disappoint. \n\nI kept it simple with the soft shell crab over drunken noodles and it was pretty fantastic. The crab was cooked perfectly and the flavor on the noodles and accompanying vegetables was great with a perfect spice level to my liking. Can't remember exactly what my wife got but I do recall constantly reaching over to take more.\n\nReally the only reason I want to drive to California again is to stop here. Also the food came out incredibly fast.", "We experienced a hugely overrated large Thai Restaurant with a simple and airy atmosphere. The food I ordered was cooked \"Thai Street Food\" style. I know this, actually having lived almost a year in Bangkok, Thailand. Not only did our waiter lie to us about the our order, but charged us a dollar more than the menu price without warning. It was not even a holiday. My glass was dirty, almost an hour to be seated, and a long wait time for an order of (obviously  cooked pre-order) \"Thai BBQ Chicken\". The off-flavor Papaya Salad was a (time and labor saving) stick cut (julienne) instead of Shredding the Papaya! ...and it was the tiniest papaya Salad that I ever saw. Th