 really glad we went for an early meal and were able to leave before the sun set. The service was pleasant and efficient: they keep things moving. It was quite busy. We showed up without a reservation on a Tuesday night around 6 p.m. and were told it would be a 30 minute wait: instead, I opted to make a reservation for the next day, and there were very few open time slots. Great price tag at the end. I have spent way, way more in Vegas for way, way less. Do not pass up on this gem.", "As far as Thai fair goes, this place definitely does the job. The food was in no way exceptional, but it was very satisfying in a way that one would expect from any decent Thai joint.\nThe Panang Curry was very tasty and cleared my sinuses nicely.\nWhat stood out to me most was the setting; situated in a derelict strip mall near DTLV, it seems like everyone who is occupying the very crowded dining room is in on a little local secret. \nOh yeah, and the price is right. $50 for an appetizer, two entrees and two beers.", "As good as advertised. Started with the egg rolls, and they were on point. Next we had the spicy vegetable soup. Got 6/10 spicy, but tasted 9/10 due to the amount of chili oil. Still, good flavor with lots of fresh veggies. For entrees, had both the fried tofu and crispy duck panang curries. The duck was exceptionally tasty. A must have. We also had the Thai tea (coconut milk based) and was also exceptional. Not too sweet and it balanced the spice in the curries. Atmosphere was comfortable, good prices, very hospitable service, and quick and efficient service. Highly recommended.", "As someone who lived in Thailand for a year this place taste like my second home it's amazing and the best thai food I have had in the USA!  :)", "Attended this restaurant following a work conference. It was highly recommend and for good reason. We shared multiple dished between five of us. Every bite was delicious. Along with everyone else I highly recommend the Garlic Prawns. Spicy sea bass