asy parking in this aging shopping center.\nLotus of Siam is a Pearl.\nChose the gloriously celebrated Garlic Shrimps : huge size, each tail holding the crisp shell and the tender meat separately : exquisitely flavored, fantastic combination of textures.\nSteak tartare issan style: being of french origin, steak tartare holds a strong attraction when listed in a reputable table menu.\nSmall super lean  prime beef(no fat whatsoever) chopped delicately in amazingly equal 1/4 inch dice with red onion, green onion, cilantro, mint, and lime thai dressing with heat to your taste... Scrumptiously refreshing heat! Not a morsel left.\n\nPhotos of famous intlly known chefs chefs adorn the walls, a rather impressive cellar is glassed in for all diners of all ethnicities to see. Bonus: they have 3 types of Nigori Sake ;)\n\nSticky Rice and Mango yo close my culinary flash back\n\nFood arrived hot and very timely.\nEfficient friendly wait staff\n\nIt's all good, and now i can share my taste and invite friends and family  not to miss out once back in Las Vegas.", "Funny story, Lotus of Siam when you drive by from Sahara looks like a hole in the wall broken down place that you would never want to eat at. On 2 different occassions I planned on going there and both times when I drove by we decided to go somewhere else. About a year ago we bit the bullet and decided to try it. Surprisingly enough the front of the restaraunt is in the back and we were basically looking at the back of the place when driving by. It can be deceiving. I've been there 1/2 dozen times since. Last night we went and there was a 1 hour - 1.5 hour wait to get seated. The foods so good we waited over an hour.\n\nI've read reviews from more than one food critic calling is the best Thai Food in all of North America. I've been to Thailand for a month to train and the food is actually better at Lotus of Siam! The owner apparently started cooking in Thailand at age 5 with her mother/grandmother and brough that experience to Vegas. Just yesterday I saw on Yahoo that Lotus of Siam was #89 on the list of the best 101 restaraunts in the USA.\n\nAs for the food, some things I recommened for an appetizer are the Prawns in a blanket, spicy chilli chicken wings and also the Tom Kah Kai Soup. For dessert the Mango Sticky Rice is the bomb. \n\nI went with 3 people total and for our main courses to split we got Crispy garlic prawns, Panang Curry and Sea bass over drunken noodles. I've had numerous dishes here and they are all good. All the curries are great, the pad thai, the crispy duck. Great flavors and taste you wont find many other places. I see myself going back very soon!", "GET THE SHRIMP!!!\n\nSecond time here. Just as fantastic as the first time. \n\nSoft shell crab drunken noodle is bombbb too\n\nJust come and eat here already!!", "Get the crispy duck with panang sauce or ask them to do it with prawns. Sea bass drunken noodles was good and the pork stew was also amazing.  So good we went for dinner and went back for lunch 2 days later.", "Get there early, and enjoy! There was a line at 5:30 pm. but worth the wait! We all had seafood meals and appetizers full of flavor! We all were super satisfied and  the service was awesome! We were just visiting Las Vegas and had remembered the restaurant from an Anthony Bourdain show ! Really glad we checked it out! We ended our dessert with the fried wonton bananas and coconut ice cream a wonderful companion pair!", "Great food and great service.  Make sure to arrive on time and make reservations days in advance.", "Great food but a little on the crowded side for me. Ambiance 2 stars becuase of the lack of personal space and small seating. Although the food is great it is hard to enjoy when stuffed in a room. So food 4 or 5 stars.", "Great food.  hard to get someone to answer the phone to make a reservation", "Great variety, huge menu, very authentic. Cheap prices for great quality food. And the service was wonderful!", "HI folks, Its Richar