y are deep fried and tossed in garlic and white pepper. The shell was the best part! So crispy, salty, slightly spicy, and not the least bit oily. It was just endless crunchfuls of deliciousness. MUST GET. These fried shells are better than chips. Better than fried pork skins. Better than any crunchy savory combo item you can ever dream of. GET THESE. They are expensive.\n\nThe coconut ice cream was very interesting. Order it. Creamy yet refreshing, it had a flavor almost similar to taro.\n\nOther stuff were whatever. The portions here are small. Be prepared to spend more here than at your regular Thai restaurant.\n\nAlso, we tried to get a thai ice tea to go and the waiter told us they were out of to-go cups... while standing in front of a huge unopened bag of plastic cups......", "May be my favorite restaurant, period. Their shrimp dishes (especially garlic shrimp, grilled shrimp) are like nothing else you've ever tried. The best thing to do is ask the waiters what they suggest. No lie, every single dish here is amazing.", "My fiance and I went there on 6/18 for breakfast.  We had 2 omelettes with 3 pancakes.  I must say everything was awesome. The server and people working there were very nice and efficient. It only took a few minutes to get our food and it was very good.  Unlike most mainstream IHOP or Denny's type restaurants, the food had lots of flavor and the servings were very large.  The pancakes were as large as the plate and tasted terrific. You can tell that the restaurant is old and in need of some updates...but who cares.  Great food and prices.  Our large omelettes with potatoes and toast were $8.99 a piece and our cakes were $2.99  I believe.", "My first time at this place.\nWhen my group was driving up, my cousin noticed this area, not the prettiest area.\nIn this shopping complex, half the spaces are abandoned.  There was one complex with no store name and two guards standing outside.\nAnyhow, here's my review on the food.\nWe were seated after a 