in every relevant category but not outstanding or exceptional; 3 stars means adequate--a place I would go to again but not great; 2 stars means unacceptable--a place I would not go again because it is seriously deficient in some way; 1 star is horrible, that the place  was not only unacceptable in some way but that it was exceptionally, unforgivably bad. In every case my rating is comparing the place reviewed to similar places-- thus an outstanding diner gets a 5 even though on an absolute scale its food might not be as good as that at a gourmet restaurant.", "WOW! Decided to try this place after all the raving reviews here on Yelp and Tripadvisor. \n\nIt deserves 5 star. Thinking about the thousands of places to eat in Las Vegas, from bottom to high class, Lotus of Siam is just spot on when you're craving for original Thai food. I've been a couple of times to Thailand, and this food was without a doubt perfectly made compared to Thailand. \n\nNext time I'll be in Vegas, this will be my first place to eat! Yummy!", "We did have high expectation's due to the Yelp reviews but it didn't meet our expectations at all. We will keep our business at Ping Kao.", "We loved this place! We did the garlic prawns and the crispy duck curry dish and it was all so yummy! Went at lunch and it was crowded but no wait!", "Well what can I say !? Just Absolutely Fantastic. What to eat? order what you know or try something new, you simply can not go wrong.", "Went there for the first time, tonight, with a friend. In a word, awesome! Had the number 55, which was beef and I think Cilantro and some other stuff I can't remember, but it was amazing. Had the yellow curry with chicken as well, both dishes done to a number 2 out of 10 heat level. I'd been told they really crank up the heat and so we went for a low number. Turns out I could have gone up several notches with that, but even at level 2 there was definitely some spice and flavor. \n\nAnyway, great food, friendly and prompt service, an