ny dishes you can choose your numbered spice level, so we often ordered a few of the same dishes at different levels. My favorite dish was the Garlic Prawns. These were full of garlic flavor, large and crunchy from being fried. Many in the group enjoyed the Crispy Duck in Panang Curry. The duck is served on top, and you mix it all into the curry. Crying Tiger Beef was another favorite of mine. While it was one of the more simple dishes, the thin beef was perfectly cooked to medium rare, and the jus on the side completed the dish. \n\nFor dessert, I loved the Coconut Ice Cream. They make it with real coconut. It was so light and icy, almost a sorbet texture, while being full of coconut flavor. A great find and a great meal overall.", "awesome and authentic- You want to try this!  We went without reservations and it was worth the wait-- looks like the out-of-towners of found this place and are turning it into a Mecca for Thai", "best thai food on the face of the earth, without question - that is all.", "great place - order off the back of the menu!", "i must say it is between a 3.5-4, not a 5 stars, because they are pricier than some of the other thai places I eat , there food is not that much better.. Service was prompt. the neighborhood is a little shady, the sign posted at the front door says there has been car breakins, make sure you don't leave any valuables in car..I don't recall any real lunch special, but lots of item to select from off the main menu, pretty much a la carte.. Plenty of parking", "looked ghetto from the outside but when we ate here Thursday afternoon not even weekends and late night it was already packed! reservations is a must but they will only hold the table for 5 mins which makes sense! so here we go, food! we ordered Thai iced tea, pretty good but not free refill.. ordrered pad Thai, garlic crispy prawns, beef fried rice... the pad Thai is good but the serving is so little it's good for one person only! garlic crispy shrimp is the best. I 