paration. If you are visiting alone or with a group of 30 this is the place to go! Local tip: If you show up when they open (5:30) for dinner without a reservation, expect a 5-15 minute wait. 6-8:30pm expect a wait of 1hr+, after 8:30 10-20 minutes depending on the day. Make a reservation ahead of time, and don't be more than 5 minutes late or they'll cancel it.", "Best thai food! Penang curry is a must! Shady looking place from\nOutside but pleasently surprized once inside. There will be a wait...worth the great food!", "Came here during a business trip. Delicious food, great service, good environment", "Came here off of a recommendation. Food was great. I will be back soon.", "Come here expecting to get an average Thai meal with above average service and atmosphere and you will not be disappointed", "Could go on and on .... And on. Treat yourself and put yourself and in the trust hands of your service - follow their recommendations and get ready for a spectacular dining experience.  I can't even remember the names of our dishes but all were: wow!", "Could go on and on .... And on. Treat yourself and put yourself and trust let your server pick your meal - follow their recommendations and get ready for a spectacular dining experience.  I can't even remember the names of our dishes but all were: wow!", "Despite the price, the food is wonderful! I recommend the soft shell crab with cabbage under I believe. This place is to die for. I would go here every time I visit Vegas. Op.", "Don't plan on staying and enjoying any conversation with friends. You order, eat and are rushed out so someone else can have your table. Food may be good but that made he whole experience unpleasant.", "Don't worry about curb appeal, just get inside this place.  It is fantastic  Some of the best Thai food I have ever had and I may go as far to say it was the BEST Thai food I have ever had...\n\nWe waited to get in but they have a great system that you can check from your phone to see how long