 place had uhmm.... grown slightly :)  Last time we were there this was a tiny restaurant but now it's rather giant and the line up to it was at a glance more than 40 ppl.  LOL. MAKE A RESERVATION! \nWell, we come for the sweet and sour chicken which is perfect here.  The sauce is perfectly spectacular and they make it just as spicy as you want which for me is \"tears in your eyes, flames in your mouth hot\" :) .  The chicken quality is great -- fresh and perfect.  The service is great -- the staff were very attentive and nice.  I'm very happy to say that despite having grown this place had not lost the quality of its food which is a HUGE relief since it's one of our favorite Thai places.", "I recently purchased Carpet and Lament flooring from Budget Flooring. The price and service was great. I will do it again 10 years from now.\nThanks again, Wayne Whiteman", "I spent a lot of time in San Francisco and I've got to be almost all the really bomb spots and Chinatown in downtown... This place is a world-class level... I highly recommend if you're in Vegas and want Chinese food stop by and check these guys out you won't be disappointed...Fried rice appetizer are on another level....Fried duck and shrimp drunken noodles Are a must try awesome", "I thought this place was phenomenal! With great, friendly/informative service and a great atmosphere, I really enjoyed my experience here. The noodles that they use for the pad thai were different than what I was accustomed to, but I thought it was great!!", "I travel in an RV all over the country. I am always looking for a good Thai restaurant. Thanks to Yelp, I found this one. I had pad woon sen and it may have been the best I have ever found. The staff was friendly.", "I've been coming here for years, originally for the lunch buffet and now for the occasional dinner. It's a little pricey and always packed in the evenings, and for good reason. This food is top notch, better than Komol or any other Thai restaurant I've been to in town. It's an an unassuming, unimpressive, and perhaps uninviting strip mall, but this area's always been home to a mix of dives and delights, don't judge the book by it's cover or the guy hitting you up for money in the parking lot.\n\nOnce inside, you'll see the space is kept up well and has a substantial wine collection. I can't comment on that since I've always thrown all my money into food and sometimes a thai tea. Their signature cuisine is northern Thai, and while I don't have other cuisine from that region to compare it to, it is delicious. That said, so are the more traditional dishes. The orange chicken, which was good during the lunch buffet, is outstanding when made to order. The pineapple fried rice has a great depth of flavor and is well-seasoned. Anything with crispy duck is excellent. The last time we had a northern Thai shrimp curry that was top notch. If you're not picky, just give the server some general parameters and they'll take care of it for you. You want a curry, pineapple rice, and crispy duck dish? Say no more. I haven't had something for dinner yet that I felt was \"meh.\" The only problem, if you can call it that, is that the menu is huge which can make it tough to decide but on the other hand always provides some room to explore. \n\nThis is a Vegas must. Call ahead to find out the wait time and see if you can put your name on the list. Expect a 45 minute wait for take-out. Don't think you can waltz in for dinner, any day of the week, without a 30 minute wait.", "I've been dying to eat at Lotus of Siam, so last week when I was in Vegas I made sure we had a reservation. \n\nI was not disappointed. \n\nThe garlic prawns were especially delicious. The prawns and skins are fried separately, then tossed in a sweet garlic sauce before serving. I had never eaten shrimp shells like this before and was completely mesmerized. Like the menu description, they really had the consistency of potato chips! \n\nThe only negative I can find is that th