 that room into a dinning area instead of a waiting room)\n\nEventually after 30 minutes we were seated.  YAY!  \nWe already knew what we wanted so at that time I sat and looked at all the photos on the wall of celebrities who ate at Lotus of Siam.  \n\nFood: \nCrispy duck with panang\nNAM KAO TOD: (Crispy rice mixed with sour cubed pork sausages, cilantro, green onions, grounded dry chilis, ginger, peanuts and lime juice)\nThai Fried Rice\nDRUNKEN NOODLE PRAWNS\n\nFoodGasmn!  The food was full of bold flavors and delicious.  Definitely a place to visit whenever I'm in Vegas.", "Located in Shopping Center and not facing Sahara so slow down before you get there.\nWorth the 30-45 minute wait. \nOne of the best Thai restaurants in Vegas if not the Southwest.", "Long wait but the food was worth it. Fried bananas and coconut ice cream dessert...yes please", "Lots of people told me I had to check this place out when I was in Vegas. Since I knew they had Northern Thai dishes that's the route I took. I had Khao Soi ( the best I've ever had) and a dish with pork and jack fruit that they recommended. I was not head over heals for the dish with the jack fruit ( you actually could barely tell there was jack fruit it blended in well, it just wasn't my favorite). If I could I'd give this place 4.5 stars ( it wasn't quite deserving of 5 in my mind). I was stuck in a little back room and felt a bit neglected. The server came around but I feel like I was forgotten about half the time. On the other hand I came with my luggage and they were very sweet and put it in their wine storage room ( they have a huge wine selection by the way). \nI'll be back next time I go to Vegas. Hopefully I won't be by myself so I can try more of the dishes. Also if anyone is wondering it was about a 12 dollar Uber from the middle of the strip.", "Lotus of Siam got off on the wrong foot with their call confirming our reservation in which they threatened to give away our reservation if we were more than fiv