od size (see picture).  For what most everyone raves about here, I will say it is good, it is tasty, but the star of the restaurant?  Only for people who are novels to it.  Would I order it again?  Yes.  But I would tell my table its one of the entrees that are good here, not the, \"OMG WE HAVE TO ORDER THISSSSSS.\"\n\nPanang -  Decent.  Nothing to write home about.\n\nGreen Curry - Forgettable.  Wait, we had green curry?\n\nSea Bass -  Totally overpriced and small portion.  Skip this.  Nuff said.  This dish is almost a whole Star doc worthy.\n\nFried Banana with Coconut Ice Cream Dessert - Delicious.  Small chunks of banana fried in an egg roll style.  The delicate thin crispiness was very well appreciated by my mouth.  The coconut ice cream was light and heavenly.  Must Order Dish.\n\nVibe - Great.  The whole place is hummin along, happy, eatin, drinkin, laughing.  It is like all my Thai friends.  \n\nThe menu here is huge.  North and South.  Most of the good dishes seem to come from Northern menu.  We enjoyed it here but like I said, the dishes seemed rushed, but for understandable reasons.  Glad to have tried it.  Come back on next Vegas trip?  Probably not (mainly because Vegas has so many options).  \n\nBut damn that Khao Soy callin my name......", "This is a wanna be fancy restaurant when it's in a junky ghetto plaza and then they didn't change the carpet when it carpet is a 1970s carpet. They put in a wine rack and lots of wine selection but don't change the carpet. They need to do the whole shebang. \n\nI had lunch special chicken curry. It was good and it has grape in it. I thought that was unique but not fancy. Like I said they is a wanna be fancy.", "This is hands down the best Thai Restaurant I've ever eaten at!!! The seafood drunken noodles are to die for, the bar has definitely been raised after eating here!", "This is the best place ever!! I will always recommend this place to my friends", "This is truly one of the best meals I've ever had.\n\nI'm a 